NAME int bit.bor (int... input)
DESCRIPTION Performs bitwise OR (input|input) over all arguments.
LINK #bit.bor
DETAILS
Bitwise OR is another very interesting function in that it can be used to make 
sure that a given bitstring's some bit is 1, or set it to 1. You can use it as 
a sort of 'on switch'. 

      1100 1100
    | 0011 0011
    = 1111 1111